From 4bcc2cb3d3d8884dede0199f75928f13933ff895 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ben Browning <bbrownin@redhat.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 23:45:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] [Frontend] Remove legacy Qwen3 parsers in favor of
 engine-based replacements

The engine-based Qwen3Parser has fully replaced the hand-written
Qwen3CoderToolParser and Qwen3ReasoningParser. Delete the legacy
implementations (~820 lines), point the "mimo" registry aliases at
the engine adapters, and consolidate redundant test fixtures.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

Signed-off-by: Ben Browning <bbrownin@redhat.com>
